department: Art of Africa and the Americas
description:
(found in collection 4/29/97)
.1 head wearing broad, short headdress consisting of 3 bands of decoration; traces of red pigment; large ears; open mouth; .2 triangular-shaped head with long neck; .3 broad head with large hoop earrings; hair gathered at either side of forehead; .4 head with flat nose, slit eyes, and slit mouth; remnants of headdress and possibly a necklace on PR side; .5 feline head with large eyes and open mouth
title: Head, one of five
